38
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,160
Hello, Xiao Rang.

39
00:01:47,960 --> 00:01:49,120
My signal is bad here.

40
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,640
Can you hear me?

41
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,080
Hello?

42
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,760
Can you hear me?

43
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:01,040
Xiao Rang.

44
00:02:01,280 --> 00:02:02,920
You're at the Binhai Grand Hotel, right?

45
00:02:02,920 --> 00:02:03,920
Wait for me there.

46
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,680
I'll be there soon, okay?

47
00:02:48,883 --> 00:02:52,960
=Episode 16=
(The Taste of the Sea)

48
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:07,840
Morning, sir.

49
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:08,560
Hello.

50
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:11,040
Where are you headed?

51
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:13,400
I'm going to your restaurant.

52
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:15,040
The biggest one.

53
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:18,120
Sir, this is a high-end hotel.

54
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:20,280
You can't enter without shoes.

55
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:24,120
What should I do? They're broken.

56
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:27,920
Sir,

57
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,920
they smell like salted fish.

58
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:33,680
I just stepped in trash.

59
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:35,920
Okay, wait a moment.

60
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,400
Here, sir.

61
00:03:41,760 --> 00:03:42,480
Wear these.

62
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,480
Thank you.

63
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:46,920
Your high-end hotel

64
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,280
services really are exceptional.

65
00:03:48,560 --> 00:03:49,360
Certainly.

66
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:52,640
Oh, so comfortable.

67
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,400
Could you throw these away for me?

68
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,000
Uh...

69
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:57,840
Okay, I'll do it.

70
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,200
Oh, no. I'll do it.

71
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:00,280
Let me help.

72
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,280
Thanks.

73
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,640
Don't wait for Li Yanhao.

74
00:04:42,560 --> 00:04:43,920
I can't eat another bite.

75
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:45,960
If we hadn't come early,

76
00:04:45,960 --> 00:04:47,240
would we have got the good food?

77
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:47,800
Eat up.

78
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,080
Don't make me eat alone.

79
00:04:49,080 --> 00:04:51,080
Didn't we have breakfast this morning?

80
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:52,960
Is that the same?

81
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:54,200
What did he make for us?

82
00:04:54,200 --> 00:04:55,240
That bland soup.

83
00:04:55,480 --> 00:04:56,960
But this? It's so delicious!

84
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:57,800
Grand hotel,

85
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,760
you know, is quite different.

86
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:01,480
Do you see that bar behind us?

87
00:05:02,080 --> 00:05:04,680
Those drinks are free!

88
00:05:04,920 --> 00:05:05,760
Really?

89
00:05:05,960 --> 00:05:07,200
I'll grab some. Want anything?

90
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:08,480
No. I want to eat more.

91
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:13,800
Then let's eat first.

92
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:17,984
Okay.

93
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:28,640
Li Yanhao, over there!

94
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:31,840
How did you get into

95
00:05:31,840 --> 00:05:33,080
such a high-end place?

96
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:34,680
Well, thanks to Yu Lan.

97
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:36,120
She came here for a seminar

98
00:05:36,120 --> 00:05:38,240
and said there was a free meal voucher.

99
00:05:38,240 --> 00:05:39,080
So we came over.

100
00:05:40,080 --> 00:05:40,960
How did you get in?

101
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:43,080
No one is at the entrance,
so I just came in.

102
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:45,680
It's almost closing time. No one cares.

103
00:05:45,680 --> 00:05:47,080
Exactly. Hurry and grab some food.

104
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,120
I'm not hungry.

105
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:50,080
Try this, it's really great.

106
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:51,800
I really don't want any. Here, take it.

107
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:52,560
Try some.

108
00:05:56,928 --> 00:05:57,520
Why do I feel

109
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:59,120
something stinks after you arrived?

110
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,240
Pass me that Kimchi.

111
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:01,120
Let me smell it.

112
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,480
Maybe some of the seafood stinks.

113
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,640
I... I'll go to the restroom.

114
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:11,760
You guys go head.

115
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:17,560
The plum wine is
sour and sweet. Amazing!

116
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:18,200
You want some?

117
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:18,760
No, thanks.

118
00:06:18,760 --> 00:06:19,840
I'm going surfing later.

119
00:06:20,040 --> 00:06:21,080
Surfing while drunk,

120
00:06:21,080 --> 00:06:22,400
you're the wildest one.

121
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:29,400
Here you come.

122
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,560
I went to the beach for shooting.

123
00:06:33,560 --> 00:06:34,680
Go eat something.

124
00:06:35,280 --> 00:06:36,520
Already ate, you guys go ahead.

125
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,960
You're Li Yanhao, right?

126
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,840
After the last student union conference,

127
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:46,480
Yu Lan always says you are talented.

128
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:49,040
You've started your movie?

129
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:50,280
Right.

130
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:50,920
This morning,

131
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:52,920
I went to the beach scouting locations.

132
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:54,560
That's great.

133
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:56,920
I've been interested in you before.

134
00:06:57,480 --> 00:06:58,960
And with Yu Lan's introduction,

135
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,200
I'm even more interested.

136
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:00,760
Thank you.

137
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:03,240
So, at this afternoon's seminar,

138
00:07:03,240 --> 00:07:04,760
I'd like you to give a speech.

139
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,200
Maybe it's a bit sudden.

140
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:10,080
Gu Ran mentioned that you're here.

141
00:07:10,080 --> 00:07:10,960
Kang said

142
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:13,040
that I highly recommended you
as a contestant.

143
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:15,240
So we decided to let you give a speech.

144
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:16,760
Cherish this opportunity.

145
00:07:17,080 --> 00:07:17,920
Make the most of it.

146
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,280
Sure, absolutely.

147
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,240
Alright, I'll go to the restroom.

148
00:07:22,760 --> 00:07:23,520
You guys chat.

149
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:26,240
Let me tell you,

150
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:28,640
this plum wine must be drunk properly.

151
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:31,360
You can't just drink it.
You need to eat the plums

152
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:32,520
to get the full essence.

153
00:07:32,920 --> 00:07:33,640
Give it a try.

154
00:07:34,080 --> 00:07:34,920
Really?

155
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:36,520
You need to eat two at once.

156
00:07:37,760 --> 00:07:38,280
Two plums?

157
00:07:38,280 --> 00:07:39,760
Right, for taste balance.

158
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,960
Then take a big gulp.

159
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,480
The flavor really comes alive.

160
00:07:48,080 --> 00:07:48,920
Want to try?

161
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,520
Try one.

162
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:52,480
Come on.

163
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,400
Try it.

164
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,040
Right?

165
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:56,840
That's good!

166
00:07:57,840 --> 00:07:58,920
I need another bottle.

167
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:01,640
Not so good.

168
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:07,960
The plum is really intoxicating.

169
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:09,640
I'm feeling drunk.

170
00:08:09,920 --> 00:08:11,200
Not bad, right?

171
00:08:17,960 --> 00:08:19,240
Try four this time.

172
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:20,920
Okay.

173
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,920
The seafood doesn't seem very fresh.

174
00:08:28,560 --> 00:08:30,120
I'll arrange the meeting room in a bit.

175
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:31,040
Come with me.

176
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,760
No.

177
00:08:32,840 --> 00:08:34,040
I'll go find Gu Ran.

178
00:08:34,120 --> 00:08:35,120
Then you should hurry up.

179
00:08:35,120 --> 00:08:37,120
I have many people to introduce you to.

180
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:37,840
Okay.

181
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,000
What have you eaten?

182
00:08:42,160 --> 00:08:44,040
I feel like the seafood isn't fresh.

183
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:45,480
Pick some fresh ones.

184
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:46,560
Don't get a stomachache.

185
00:08:47,480 --> 00:08:48,800
Thank you, Kang.

186
00:08:48,800 --> 00:08:50,000
Wipe your mouth.

187
00:08:50,920 --> 00:08:52,320
Yu Lan, I'll wait for you there.

188
00:08:53,920 --> 00:08:55,040
Let me pick a plum for you.

189
00:08:55,040 --> 00:08:55,680
Good.

190
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:56,360
Okay.

191
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,720
- Okay.
- I don't eat plums.

192
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,360
Young man,

193
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,240
when you were in the restroom just now,

194
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,360
did your phone fall in?

195
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,480
No.

196
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:18,360
Then why wash so vigorously?

197
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:20,360
You almost scrub yourself bald.

198
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:23,360
I love cleanliness.

199
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:24,720
It's good.

200
00:09:28,440 --> 00:09:29,680
But that's enough.

201
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:32,600
Everyone shall save water.

202
00:09:33,160 --> 00:09:34,440
Sure.

203
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,040
I'll be quick.

204
00:09:56,160 --> 00:09:57,160
You finally come back.

205
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,600
You are back, huh?

206
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,600
What did you eat in the restroom?

207
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,880
Just eat your oysters!

208
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:09,480
I don't want these oysters.

209
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:13,320
Where is your manager?
I want to make a complaint.

210
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,600
As his girlfriend,
could you do something?

211
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:17,600
Sit down!

212
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:19,360
Alright.

213
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,720
What are you going to say
in your speech this afternoon?

214
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:29,440
Secret for now.

215
00:10:30,600 --> 00:10:32,480
There will be many experts there.

216
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:34,800
You are the only contestant
that can give a speech.

217
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:36,720
This was specially arranged by Kang.

218
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,120
You have to do your best.

219
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,880
He has invited a lot of

220
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:43,040
famous experts

221
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:44,600
and leaders from other institutions.

222
00:10:44,720 --> 00:10:47,000
The success of the film festival

223
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:47,920
must attribute to him.

224
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:48,920
Yes.

225
00:10:51,240 --> 00:10:52,120
I will try my best.

226
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,600
I will go prepare.

227
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,560
Let me see what he is eating
in the restroom.

228
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:03,104
Hey!

229
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,120
Idiot.

230
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:08,360
Distinguished leaders and teachers,

231
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,360
I am Li Yanhao

232
00:11:10,360 --> 00:11:13,720
from Library Management Department
of Binhai University.

233
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,880
It's my great honor

234
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,480
to give this speech before you.

235
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:26,600
What are you doing?

236
00:11:28,160 --> 00:11:29,560
What are you thinking about?

237
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:31,360
You scared me.

238
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:33,160
Have you prepared well for your speech?

239
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:35,720
I just wrote a few lines.

240
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:37,120
Got no clue.

241
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:39,320
That's not the truth, right?

242
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,320
You're nervous about
facing the president and Kang Yide,

243
00:11:42,680 --> 00:11:43,920
aren't you?

244
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,880
Nervous? No way.

245
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:47,800
They ask me to speak, so I will

246
00:11:47,800 --> 00:11:49,480
just talk about my plans.

247
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,240
Just with my disposable slippers,

248
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:52,560
I can convince them completely.

249
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:56,360
Then I'm relieved.

250
00:11:57,800 --> 00:11:59,240
Try your best this afternoon.

251
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,680
You are the backbone of our team.

252
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,040
Keep it up!

253
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:02,680
Don't worry.

254
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:09,120
I have a question.

255
00:12:10,040 --> 00:12:11,040
Where did you go?

256
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,800
Running by the sea and taking pictures.

257
00:12:14,120 --> 00:12:15,120
Why didn't you take me?

258
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:17,240
You were asleep at that time.

259
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:18,120
I...

260
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:21,480
Couldn't you wake me up?

261
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:24,360
Besides,

262
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:26,120
why did you come back so late?

263
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,680
You might not believe

264
00:12:28,800 --> 00:12:30,360
that I ran into my parents by the sea

265
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,800
and had breakfast with them.

266
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,040
Your parents are here?

267
00:12:35,680 --> 00:12:37,560
I've wasted such a great opportunity.

268
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,160
What do you mean?

269
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:42,720
Nothing.

270
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,680
You should have taken me with you.

271
00:12:48,040 --> 00:12:49,480
But my parents were there.

272
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:51,120
That wouldn't be appropriate.

273
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:52,800
What's inappropriate about it?

274
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,920
As the saying goes,

275
00:12:54,920 --> 00:12:57,480
an ugly bride has to meet the in-laws
sooner or later.

276
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:58,160
Besides,

277
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:00,880
I'm not ugly, right?

278
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:05,800
Isn't it a bit early to say that?

279
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:07,600
Early?

280
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:08,800
I...

281
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:10,680
Listen,

282
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,240
if you leave me behind again...

283
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,480
Next time, I promise to go with you.

284
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:16,560
Leave me alone for the next hour.

285
00:13:24,915 --> 00:13:26,208
(No Smoking)

286
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:37,560
Don't be scared, man.

287
00:13:38,040 --> 00:13:38,720
I'm fine.

288
00:13:39,480 --> 00:13:40,480
I'll just wash my face.

